Online</span></div><span class="ds2-r14 mt-ds2-4 line-clamp-3 w-full text-ds2-text-fill-tertiary-enabled" style="font-family:NeuSans, Inter, system-ui, sans-serif"><p class="mb-ds2-10"># 🚀 Builders Skill Sprint: OpenClaw Month</p>
<p class="mb-ds2-10">## Claude &#x26; OpenClaw on AWS</p>
<p class="mb-ds2-10">Join AWS User Group Madurai for a special <strong>Builders Skill Sprint</strong> dedicated to <strong>OpenClaw Month</strong>, where we'll explore how to build production-grade AI agents using <strong>Claude, OpenClaw, and AWS</strong>.<br>
This session is designed for builders who want to move beyond AI demos and learn how to create scalable, autonomous agent systems that can solve real-world problems.</p>
<p class="mb-ds2-10">### What You'll Learn</p>
<p class="mb-ds2-10">🔹 Introduction to OpenClaw and the Agentic AI ecosystem<br>
🔹 Leveraging Claude for reasoning, planning, and decision-making<br>
🔹 Building AI agents on AWS infrastructure<br>
🔹 Agent orchestration, tool calling, and workflow automation<br>
🔹 Deploying production-ready agent applications<br>
🔹 Best practices for security, monitoring, and scaling</p>
<p class="mb-ds2-10">### Builders Skill Sprint Highlights</p>
<p class="mb-ds2-10">✅ Hands-on learning experience<br>
✅ Live demos and architecture walkthroughs<br>
✅ Open-source AI agent development practices<br>
✅ Real-world use cases and implementation strategies<br>
✅ Community networking with AWS and AI builders</p>
<p class="mb-ds2-10">### Who Should Attend?</p>
<ul class="pl-5 list-disc mb-4">
<li>Developers and Software Engineers</li>
<li>Cloud &#x26; DevOps Professionals</li>
<li>AI/ML Enthusiasts</li>
<li>Solution Architects</li>
<li>Students and Emerging Builders</li>
</ul></span><div class="flex items-center text-ds2-text-fill-primary-enabled"><div class="m-ds2-8 ml-0 flex"><ul class="flex flex-row"><li class="relative first:ml-ds2-0 -ml-ds2-6" style="mask:radial-gradient(circle at 110% 50%, transparent 10px, black 8px)"><div class="relative flex items-center justify-center rounded-ds2-max size-[18px]"><div class="flex size-full select-none items-center justify-center overflow-hidden rounded-ds2-max outline-1 -outline-offset-1 outline-ds2-avatar-base-stroke-enabled [outline-style:solid]"><img alt="Photo of the user " draggable="false" aria-label="Photo of the user " loading="lazy" width="18" height="18" decoding="async" data-nimg="1" class="size-full object-cover" style="color:transparent" srcSet="https://secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/member/1/9/5/9/thumb_322026489.jpeg?w=32 1x, https://secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/member/1/9/5/9/thumb_322026489.jpeg?w=48 2x" src="https://secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/member/1/9/5/9/thumb_322026489.jpeg?w=48"/></div></div></li><li class="relative first:ml-ds2-0 -ml-ds2-6" style="mask:radial-gradient(circle at 110% 50%, transparent 10px, black 8px)"><div class="relative flex items-center justify-center rounded-ds2-max size-[18px]"><div class="flex size-full select-none items-center justify-center overflow-hidden rounded-ds2-max outline-1 -outline-offset-1 outline-ds2-avatar-base-stroke-enabled [outline-style:solid]"><img alt="Photo of the user " draggable="false" aria-label="Photo of the user " loading="lazy" width="18" height="18" decoding="async" data-nimg="1" class="size-full object-cover" style="color:transparent" srcSet="https://secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/member/1/1/3/f/thumb_318364415.jpeg?w=32 1x, https://secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/member/1/1/3/f/thumb_318364415.jpeg?w=48 2x" src="https://secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/member/1/1/3/f/thumb_318364415.jpeg?w=48"/></div></div></li><li class="relative first:ml-ds2-0 -ml-ds2-6"><div class="relative flex items-center justify-center r